Step 1: Install Pip
sudo apt install python-pip

sudo pip install --upgrade pip # If upgrade is needed

Note that it takes about 5-10 minutes to get the lock. Running this command throws the following error before that

Error:
E: Could not get lock /var/lib/dpkg/lock - open (11: Resource temporarily unavailable)
E: Unable to lock the administration directory (/var/lib/dpkg/), is another process using it?


Step 2:  
Use requirements.txt file in AWS_Help repository to install modules
git clone https://github.com/CS15B001/AWS_Help.git
sudo pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 3:
sudo pip install tensorflow-gpu==1.3 (Or required version)

Step 4:
Install htop for easy machine monitoring
sudo apt install htop

Step 5:
Use the following command to monitor NVIDIA Graphics usage
watch nvidia-smi